9.text: Had + past participle Had they invited any other schools? Yes. They had invited five other schools. The drama was good. They had practised well.

10.text: We use the past perfect tense to talk about a past action that happened before another past action.

11.text: e.g. :- By the time Mr. Perera reached the station,his train had already left.

12.text: He had worked. Had he worked? He had not worked.

14.text: Fill in the blanks with the past perfect form of the verb.

15.text: • Did you watch the film yesterday? No, I didn’t. I ……………………… (watch) it before.

16.text: • She was happy because she ……………………………….. (win) a prize.

17.text: • Mr. Perera had to go back to the office. He ………………… (leave) his spectacles behind.

18.text: • I enjoyed the play. I …………………………… (not see) a stage play before.

19.text: • …………………… the football match already …………………… (start) when you got to the stadium?
